sql:
SELECT COUNT(file_id) AS total_files_uploaded
FROM lisp_files
WHERE uploader_id = 1;

SELECT file_name, version
FROM lisp_files
ORDER BY file_name;

SELECT file_name
FROM lisp_files
ORDER BY file_name;

SELECT uploader_id, COUNT(file_id) AS file_count
FROM lisp_files
GROUP BY uploader_id;

SELECT file_name
FROM lisp_files
WHERE uploader_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
; A 'developer' refers to a user with a specific role in the system, indicating they are responsible for creating or modifying Lisp files; 
; Successful execution implies that the Lisp program ran without errors; 
; Garbage collection invocations are an important performance metric, indicating how often the system had to reclaim memory during execution.

Fastest evaluation time refers to the minimum value in the eval_time column of the performance_metrics table for each unique combination of file_id and machine_id; 

The Lisp files are ranked based on their evaluation time for each unique combination of file and machine; 

Uploader refers to the user who uploaded the Lisp file; 

Executor refers to the user who executed the file.
